            "answer_text": "The first three books should be read in the order of publication:  Foundation, Foundation and Empire, Second Foundation. The remaining books should not be read at all.  The transition between the two generations is instantly obvious:  the later books lack the sociological backbone (however improbable) that made the earlier trilogy coherent and, in its own way, grand.  Instead they have the heroes one would expect in a Young Adult novel, and plots that are about the heroes rather than about the society.   The lack of intellectual content also highlights Asimov's somewhat stiff prose.  So the books are not only dumb and condescending, but objectively poorly written. ",
