            "answer_text": "Interesting question. Of the Tolkien novels, I did read THE TWO TOWERS before FELLOWSHIP. But in the case of Asimov, I read the FOUNDATION books in order, then the Elijah Bailey novels and I, Robot. But I went on to read obscure titles few today have heard of like PEBBLE IN THE SKY, THE CURRENTS OF SPACE and THE STARS, LIKE DUST. In fact, all were rich in my thoughts when I was asked to write the final followup novel, FOUNDATION\u2019S TRIUMPH, tying together all the loose threads from all those novels, even the obscure ones. ",
